, disabling the trap and ending the petrified condition on those affected.</p><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/dutoc/209\" target=\"_new\">Dungeon Magazine 209</a>.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-24px\";\r\n                else if (c == \'miright\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-18px\";\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n</script>\r\n','');
INSERT INTO `Trap` VALUES ('1113','Muck Pit','None','Hazard','12','Dungeon Magazine 209','0','\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html>\r\n<head id=\"Head1\"><title>\r\nMuck Pit\r\n</title><meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=EmulateIE7\" /><link href=\"styles/detail.css\" media=\"screen\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/print.css\" media=\"print\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/mobile.css\" media=\"handheld\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <form name=\"form1\" method=\"post\" action=\"display.php?page=trap&amp;id=1113\" id=\"form1\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div id=\"detail\">\r\n\r\n<h1 class=\"thHead\">Muck Pit<br/><span class=\"thSubHead\">Terrain</span><br/><span class=\"thLevel\">Level 12 Hazard<span class=\"thXP\">XP 700</span></span></h1><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Detect</b> automatic</p><span class=\"thInit\"><b>Initiative</b> —</span><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Immune</b> attacks </p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Traits</h2><p class=\"th2\"><b>Sucking Mud</b> </p><p class=\"thStat\">Each square of muck costs 3 extra squares of movement to enter. A creature that ends its turn in the muck must succeed on a DC 20 Athletics check or sink 5 feet, to a maximum depth of 20 feet.</p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Triggered Actions</h2><p class=\"th2\"><img src=\"images/symbol/Z2a.gif\" /><b>Choking Filth</b> (disease, poison)  <img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" /> <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Trigger</i>: A creature starts its turn under the pit’s surface.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Attack</i>: Melee 0 (triggering creature); +15 vs. Fortitude</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Hit</i>: 3d6 + 9 poison damage.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Effect</i>: The target contracts cackle fever.</p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Countermeasures</h2><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Detect</b>: Dungeoneering or Nature DC 20 (minor action). <i>Success:</i> The character discerns the hazard’s effects.</p><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/dutoc/209\" target=\"_new\">Dungeon Magazine 209</a>.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-24px\";\r\n                else if (c == \'miright\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-18px\";\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n</script>\r\n','');
INSERT INTO `Trap` VALUES ('1114','Death Mold','None','Hazard','12','Dungeon Magazine 209','0','\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html>\r\n<head id=\"Head1\"><title>\r\nDeath Mold\r\n</title><meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=EmulateIE7\" /><link href=\"styles/detail.css\" media=\"screen\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/print.css\" media=\"print\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/mobile.css\" media=\"handheld\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <form name=\"form1\" method=\"post\" action=\"display.php?page=trap&amp;id=1114\" id=\"form1\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div id=\"detail\">\r\n\r\n<h1 class=\"thHead\">Death Mold<br/><span class=\"thSubHead\">Terrain</span><br/><span class=\"thLevel\">Level 12 Hazard<span class=\"thXP\">XP 700</span></span></h1><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Detect</b> Perception DC 20</p><span class=\"thInit\"><b>Initiative</b> —</span><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Immune</b> attacks </p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Triggered Actions</h2><p class=\"th2\"><img src=\"images/symbol/Z1a.gif\" /><b>Attack</b> (necrotic)  <img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" /> <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Trigger</i>: A living creature enters or starts its turn within 3 squares of the mold.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Attack</i> (<i>Immediate Reaction</i>): Close blast 3 (living creatures in the blast); +15 vs. Fortitude</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Hit</i>: 2d6 + 10 necrotic damage. A Small or Medium target reduced to 0 hit points or fewer dies and immediately becomes a death mold zombie. The zombie rolls initiative and acts on its turn.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Miss</i>: Half damage.</p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Countermeasures</h2><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Dormant</b>: A character can use a radiant attack power to render the death mold dormant in a target square or squares in the attack’s area. No attack roll is necessary. Until the end of the character’s next turn, the trigger does not function.</p><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Destroy</b>: A character can use a fire attack power to destroy the death mold in a target square or squares in the attack’s area. No attack roll is necessary.</p><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/dutoc/209\" target=\"_new\">Dungeon Magazine 209</a>.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-24px\";\r\n                else if (c == \'miright\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-18px\";\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n</script>\r\n','');
INSERT INTO `Trap` VALUES ('1115','Mold King\'s Casket','None','Trap','15','Dungeon Magazine 209','0','\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html>\r\n<head id=\"Head1\"><title>\r\nMold King\'s Casket\r\n</title><meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=EmulateIE7\" /><link href=\"styles/detail.css\" media=\"screen\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/print.css\" media=\"print\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/mobile.css\" media=\"handheld\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <form name=\"form1\" method=\"post\" action=\"display.php?page=trap&amp;id=1115\" id=\"form1\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div id=\"detail\">\r\n\r\n<h1 class=\"thHead\">Mold King\'s Casket<br/><span class=\"thSubHead\">Object</span><br/><span class=\"thLevel\">Level 15 Trap<span class=\"thXP\">XP 1200</span></span></h1><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Detect</b> Perception DC 22</p><span class=\"thInit\"><b>Initiative</b> —</span><p class=\"thStat\"><b>HP</b> 30</p><p class=\"thStat\"><b>AC</b> 25, <b>Fortitude</b> 25, <b>Reflex</b> 3, <b>Will</b> —</p><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Immune</b> cold, fire, necrotic, poison, psychic, radiant, forced movement, all conditions, ongoing damage </p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Triggered Actions</h2><p class=\"th2\"><img src=\"images/symbol/Z1a.gif\" /><b>Explosion</b> (fire)  <img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" /> <b>Encounter</b></p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Trigger</i>: The chest drops to 0 hit points or is opened without the key being turned in the correct sequence.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Attack</i> (<i>Immediate Reaction</i>): Close burst 4 (creatures in burst); +18 vs. Reflex</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Hit</i>: 3d10 + 10 fire damage.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Miss</i>: Half damage.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Effect</i>: The chest and its contents are destroyed.</p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Countermeasures</h2><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Disable</b>: Thievery DC 22 (standard action). <i>Success:</i> The chest is unlocked after three successes.<i> Failure (21 or less):</i> If two consecutive checks fail, or if one check result is 17 or lower, the trap triggers.</p><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/dutoc/209\" target=\"_new\">Dungeon Magazine 209</a>.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-24px\";\r\n                else if (c == \'miright\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-18px\";\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n</script>\r\n','');
INSERT INTO `Trap` VALUES ('1116','Tears of the Crocodile God','None','Lurker','15','Dungeon Magazine 209','0','\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html>\r\n<head id=\"Head1\"><title>\r\nTears of the Crocodile God\r\n</title><meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=EmulateIE7\" /><link href=\"styles/detail.css\" media=\"screen\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/print.css\" media=\"print\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/mobile.css\" media=\"handheld\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <form name=\"form1\" method=\"post\" action=\"display.php?page=trap&amp;id=1116\" id=\"form1\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div id=\"detail\">\r\n\r\n<h1 class=\"thHead\">Tears of the Crocodile God<br/><span class=\"thSubHead\">Object</span><br/><span class=\"thLevel\">Level 15 Lurker<span class=\"thXP\">XP 1200</span></span></h1><p class=\"thStat\"><b>Detect</b> see Countermeasures</p><span class=\"thInit\"><b>Initiative</b> +3</span><h2 class=\"thHead\">Triggered Actions</h2><p class=\"th2\"><b>Sand Flood</b>  <img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" /> <b>Encounter</b></p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Trigger</i>: The lizard statue is moved or the jaws of the central crocodile head are forced open.</p><p class=\"tbod\"><i>Effect</i>: Sand begins pouring into the room, and the trap rolls initiative. At the start of each of the trap’s turns, the sand’s depth increases by 1 foot to a maximum depth of 10 feet. Each square costs 1 extra square of movement to enter for every 2 feet of sand in the room. Creatures that have a burrow speed are immune to this effect.</p><h2 class=\"thHead\">Countermeasures</h2><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Detect</b>: Dungeoneering or Perception DC 22 (minor action). <i>Success:</i> The character notices that the closed jaws of the central crocodile head are hinged and operate some form of internal mechanism.</p><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Detect</b>: Dungeoneering or Perception DC 22 (move action). <i>Requirement:</i> The character must climb up to the crocodile head to examine the eye sockets (Athletics DC 20). <i>Success:</i> The character discovers that the eyelids open and close.</p><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Detect</b>: Arcana DC 30 (standard action). <i>Success:</i> The character uncovers runes written on the plinths that bind them to the four corner crocodile heads.</p><p class=\"thBody\"><img src=\"images/symbol/x.gif\" />  <b>Disable</b>: When the lizard, locust, snake, and toad statues are moved to their correct positions, the trap stops spewing sand.</p><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/dutoc/209\" target=\"_new\">Dungeon Magazine 209</a>.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-24px\";\r\n                else if (c == \'miright\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-18px\";\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n</script>\r\n','');
